ViBe (Visual Background Extractor)
----------------------------------

The ViBe background-subtraction algorithm is described in:

  O. Barnich and M. Van Droogenbroeck, "ViBe: A Universal Background
  Subtraction Algorithm for Video Sequences," IEEE Transactions on
  Image Processing, vol. 20, no. 6, pp. 1709-1724, June 2011.

ViBe is covered by patents owned by Université de Liège (ULiège),
Belgium:

  Priority filing: EP20070112011, 2007-07-08
  PCT publication: WO2009007198 (2009-01-15)
  - EP2015252B1 (Europe)
  - US 8009918 B2 (United States)
  - JP 4699564 B2 (Japan)

The ViBe-related code in this repository is an INDEPENDENT
reimplementation written from the published IEEE TIP 2011 paper and
related publications. This repository does NOT contain or distribute
the official ViBe reference code maintained by ULiège. The "Software
Evaluation License Agreement" distributed with the official ViBe
reference code therefore does not apply to this code, and does not
grant any rights under the patents above.

Additional information on the algorithm and the official reference
implementation: https://www.telecom.uliege.be/vibe/

